title: Teriyaki Chicken Ramen
summary: Teriyaki Chicken Ramen is a dairy free main course. One serving contains 420 calories, 22g of protein, and 27g of fat. For $1.28 per serving, this recipe covers 23% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe serves 4. 37 people have made this recipe and would make it again. This recipe from Life Made Sweeter requires rice vinegar, sriracha sauce optional, garlic, and broccoli florets. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 27 minutes. This recipe is typical of Japanese cuisine. Taking all factors into account, this recipe earns a spoonacular score of 79%, which is good. Try Beef with Broccoli Teriyaki and Ramen Noodles, Teriyaki Vegetable Stir-fry with Ramen Noodles, and Teriyaki Chicken Wings w/ fresh Teriyaki Sauce for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are great choices for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. The NV Amber Falls Winery Sarah's Choice Riesling with a 5 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 16 dollars per bottle.

instructions:
Instructions



In a large wok or skillet, prepare the noodles according to package directions. Drain and set aside. Meanwhile, season chicken with salt, black pepper and 1 teaspoon sesame oil. Set aside.


After the noodles are finished, drain pan and wipe down with a clean damp towel. Heat over medium-high heat. Add 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil and saute chicken until cooked through, about 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate.


Return pan to heat and add remaining olive oil. Add the garlic, ginger, broccoli, grated carrots and edamame beans. Cook until the vegetables are just crisp tender, about 2-3 minutes.


Meanwhile, whisk together the soy sauce, brown sugar, remaining 2 teaspoons sesame oil, rice vinegar, cornstarch and water. Stir into pan along with the cooked chicken and prepared ramen noodles. Allow sauce to bubble and thicken up and toss to coat well. Adjust seasonings with salt and pepper as needed plus chili flakes or Sriracha if desired.


Serve hot topped with sesame seeds and green onions, if desired.
